pullRequest.bodyText:
Fixes #9423.
A bit of context
None of the links to other question cards on the same page worked because:


they referred to the yet non-existing ids,


passive links used hrefs when they should be using routerLinks instead (see a similar issue for Angular 5 or above discussed on StackOverflow).


Desired behavior is to jump to the specific question card once the link is pressed. The question card's content (i.e. answer to the question) should be collapsed. Otherwise, the behavior may be confusing to the user.
Outline of Solution
Thus, the solution was carried out as follows:

All the missing ids of the template elements were added;
'Jumping' to questions was implemented with a method that scrolls into the specified question (as, unfortunately, using data-target attributes for anchor tags turned out to be non-working or buggy/messy for Angular 8. Correct me if I am wrong);
Passive links were built using RouterModule's routerLink attribute;
Collapsing question contents was implemented with simply toggling corresponding boolean values for NgbCollapse directive;
Toggling boolean values from other components was implemented with a simple data sharing service;
A simple test was added for a data sharing service.

I must admit that in some places this solution is not the most elegant and quite 'hacky'. In particular, see items 4 and 5 that describe how 'collapsing question contents' was implemented. Nonetheless, as far as I could see from a quite through web/documentation search, these are the best alternatives available. I am just a beginner in Angular development, though, so, if anyone can give hints/advice/ideas on a better workaround, I would be thankful.

